{"title_page": "Mike Repole", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Mike Repole\n| image         = <!-- Nothing on Wikimedia Commons -->\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1969|01|21}}\n| birth_place   = [[Middle Village, Queens|Middle Village]], Queens, [[New York City|NY]]\n| death_date    = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (DEATH date then BIRTH date)  -->\n| death_place   = \n| residence     = [[Long Island]], NY\n| nationality   = American\n| alma mater    = St. John's University\n| occupation    = Founder, vitamin water\n| spouse        = Maria\n| children      = 1\n| parents       = Annie & Benny Repole\n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n'''Mike Repole''' (born January 21, 1969) is an American entrepreneur, businessman, and owner of Repole Stables, best known for co-founding [[Glaceau]] (maker of [[Vitaminwater]]), which sold to [[Coca-Cola]] for $4.1&nbsp;billion, and [[BODYARMOR SuperDrink]], a [[sports drink]] manufacturer.\n\n==Personal life==\nRepole was born on January 21, 1969 in [[Middle Village, Queens|Middle Village]] [[Queens]], New York City to mother Annie Repole, a [[seamstress]], and father Benny Repole, a waiter. Repole's parents, Italian immigrants, were devout [[Catholics]].<ref name=\"Forbes - parents\">{{cite web |last1=Burns |first1=Mark J. |title=Think Big, Dream Bigger: Mike Repole's Journey To Becoming Co-Founder Of BODYARMOR |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/markjburns/2014/10/13/think-big-dream-bigger-mike-repoles-journey-to-becoming-co-founder-of-bodyarmor/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=August 21, 2018 }}</ref><ref name=\"newsday 2\">{{cite web |title=Winning Belmont would be special for Repole and Viola |url=https://www.newsday.com/sports/horseracing/belmont-stakes/belmont-repole-viola-vino-rosso-1.19013847 |website=Newsday |accessdate=August 21, 2018 }}</ref> He grew up in Middle Village, and attended [[Middle Village, Queens#Schools|St. Margaret's Elementary]] and [[Holy Cross High School (Queens)|Holy Cross High School]]. Repole, the first in his family to go to college, went to [[St. John's University (New York City)|St. John's University]] and graduated with a degree in Sports Administration.<ref name=\"parade\">{{cite web |last1=Osacky |first1=Michael |title=Interview with Entrepreneur and Visionary Mike Repole |url=https://parade.com/345070/michaelosacky/interview-with-entrepreneur-and-visionary-mike-repole/ |website=Parade |accessdate=August 21, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nRepole lives in Long Island with his wife Maria and their daughter.<ref name=\"newsday 2\" /><ref name=\"newsday 1\">{{cite web |last1=McNamara |first1=Ed |title=LI's Mike Repole gets another chance in Derby |url=https://www.newsday.com/sports/horseracing/another-shot-at-the-derby-for-li-s-mike-repole-1.18375519 |website=Newsday |accessdate=August 21, 2018 }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nRepole first began his career at [[Dr Pepper Snapple Group|Mistic Beverages]]. He later joined [[Crystal Geyser]] as Vice President of Sales. In 1999, Repole co-founded, with [[J. Darius Bikoff]], [[Energy Brands]], commonly known as Glaceau, which produced Smartwater and Vitaminwater, and which was credited with launching the [[enhanced water]] beverage vertical.<ref name=\"forbes 2\">{{cite web |last1=Heitner |first1=Darren |title=Father of BODYARMOR Speaks About Plan To Disrupt The Sports Drink Industry |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/darrenheitner/2014/06/15/father-of-bodyarmor-speaks-about-plan-to-disrupt-the-sports-drink-industry/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=August 21, 2018 }}</ref> The company grew quickly, netting $1M in its first year, and growing to over $1&nbsp;billion in sales by 2007, when it was the top-selling water brand in the US. In 2007, Coca-Cola bought the company for $4.1&nbsp;billion.<ref name=\"INC\">{{cite web |last1=Heitner |first1=Darren |title=Meet the Successful Entrepreneur Seeking a Triple Crown |url=https://www.inc.com/darren-heitner/a-look-at-the-beverage-businessman-seeking-a-triple-crown.html |website=Inc.com |accessdate=August 21, 2018 |date=May 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, he joined [[Pirate's Booty]] as [[chairman of the board]]. He helped the company grow 300% in less than five years. In 2013, Pirate Brands sold for $195&nbsp;million to [[B&G Foods]].<ref name=\"forbes 2\" /><ref name=\"St Johns\">{{cite web |title=Mike Repole \u201991SVC St. John's University |url=https://www.stjohns.edu/academics/schools-and-colleges/college-professional-studies/success-stories/mike-repole-91svc |website=stjohns.edu |accessdate=August 21, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, he co-founded BodyArmor Superdrink, a [[sports drink]]s company, with Lance Collins.<ref name=\"forbes 2\" /> BodyArmor, usually stylized BODYARMOR, garnered media attention in 2014 when [[Kobe Bryant]], a professional [[basketball]] player, invested millions into the company and became the company's creative director. Bryant is additionally the fourth largest stakeholder in the company, and Repole currently serves as Chairman of the company.<ref name=\"ESPN\">{{cite news |last1=Rovell |first1=Darren |title=Kobe's $6M drink investment has $200M return |url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/24384862/kobe-bryant-6m-investment-sports-drink-now-worth-200m |accessdate=August 22, 2018 |publisher=ESPN |date=August 16, 2018 }}</ref> In August 2018, Coca-Cola became the second largest stakeholder in BodyArmor in an attempt to further challenge rival [[Pepsi]]'s hold, via its [[Gatorade]] brand, on the sport's drink industry.<ref name=\"parade\" /> According to [[Nielsen Corporation|Nielsen]] data, BodyArmor is the third most purchased sports drink, with expected revenues of $400&nbsp;million in 2018.<ref name=\"WSJ\">{{cite news |last1=Maloney |first1=Jennifer |last2=Lombardo |first2=Cara |title=Coca-Cola Invests in BodyArmor as It Chases Gatorade |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/coca-cola-invests-in-bodyarmor-as-it-chases-gatorade-1534237201 |accessdate=August 22, 2018 |work=The Wall Street Journal |date=August 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Repole co-starred in the [[Barstool Sports]] investment show \u201cBig Brain,\u201d where he served as a financial advisor to [[Dave Portnoy]], alongside [[Jon Taffer]].\n\n===Repole Stable===\nRepole became a [[horse racing]] fan in his teenage years.<ref name=\"NYP\">{{cite news |last1=Maloney |first1=Jennifer |last2=Lombardo |first2=Cara |title=Belmont Stakes is only race that matters for this Queens owner |url=https://nypost.com/2018/06/04/belmont-stakes-is-only-race-that-matters-for-this-queens-owner/ |accessdate=August 22, 2018 |work=New York Post |date=June 5, 2018}}</ref> During his time at Glaceau, he became increasingly involved in horse racing and [[thoroughbred]] ownership, and, after selling Glaceau, he opened Repole Stable. His most accomplished horse, [[Uncle Mo]], was named the [[American Champion Two-Year-Old Male Horse|American Champion Two-Year-Old]] in 2010, and is currently one of the most popular racehorse [[sire]]s, having sired [[Kentucky Derby]] winner [[Nyquist (horse)|Nyquist]], among others.<ref name=\"Kentucky.com\">{{cite news |last1=Peck |first1=Jared |title=Who owns every Kentucky Derby horse and how they got so rich |url=https://www.kentucky.com/sports/horses/kentucky-derby/article209438674.html |accessdate=August 22, 2018 |work=kentucky |date=May 2, 2018 }}</ref> Repole's horse, [[Vino Rosso]], won the [[Breeders' Cup Classic]] in 2019. The stables' other notable horses include Coach Inge, [[Notacatbutallama]], [[Caixa Eletronica]] and multiple [[Graded stakes race|Grade 1]] winner [[Stay Thirsty]].<ref name=\"ABR\">{{cite web |title=Repole Stable |url=https://www.americasbestracing.net/owners/repole-stable |website=americasbestracing.net |accessdate=August 22, 2018 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Repole, Micheal}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American food company founders]]\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:St. John's University (New York City) alumni]]\n[[Category:American chief executives of food industry companies]]\n[[Category:American racehorse owners and breeders]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Mike Repole\n| image         = <!-- Nothing on Wikimedia Commons -->\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|1969|01|21}}\n| birth_place   = [[Middle Village, Queens|Middle Village]], Queens, [[New York City|NY]]\n| death_date    = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (DEATH date then BIRTH date)  -->\n| death_place   = \n| residence     = [[Long Island]], NY\n| nationality   = American\n| alma mater    = St. John's University\n| occupation    = Founder, vitamin water\n| spouse        = Maria\n| children      = 1\n| parents       = Annie & Benny Repole\n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n'''Mike Repole''' (born January 21, 1969) is an American entrepreneur, businessman, and owner of Repole Stables, best known for co-founding [[Glaceau]] (maker of [[Vitaminwater]]), which sold to [[Coca-Cola]] for $4.1&nbsp;billion, and [[BODYARMOR SuperDrink]], a [[sports drink]] manufacturer.\n\n==Personal life==\nRepole was born on January 21, 1969 in [[Middle Village, Queens|Middle Village]] [[Queens]], New York City to mother Annie Repole, a [[seamstress]], and father Benny Repole, a waiter. Repole's parents, Italian immigrants, were devout [[Catholics]].<ref name=\"Forbes - parents\">{{cite web |last1=Burns |first1=Mark J. |title=Think Big, Dream Bigger: Mike Repole's Journey To Becoming Co-Founder Of BODYARMOR |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/markjburns/2014/10/13/think-big-dream-bigger-mike-repoles-journey-to-becoming-co-founder-of-bodyarmor/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=Aug